        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 7:26PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 726 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bella Vista, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Powell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
